scripts.test:playground:create-files:
rm -rf tmp/playground && mkdir -p tmp/playground && cp .env* tmp/playground/ 2>/dev/null || true && echo '# @niquola/tsql Testing Playground

This playground allows you to test the published package locally.

## Available Tests

- `node test.cjs` - CommonJS test (recommended)
- `node test.mjs` - ESM test (may have bundling issues with pg dependency)

## Package Exports

The package exports:
- `Database` - Main database class
- `QueryBuilder` - Query building utilities
- `createQueryBuilder` - Factory function
- `getDatabaseConfig` - Configuration utilities
- `getDatabaseUrl` - URL utilities

## Example Usage

```javascript
const { Database } = require("@niquola/tsql");

// Create database instance
const db = new Database({ connectionString: "your-connection-string" });
```
